msgctxt "sn3.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Shackles"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 3. Jarāmaraṇasutta → rājasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | rājā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn3.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Jarāmaraṇasutta"
msgstr "3. Old Age and Death"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.71"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.164"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.3:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.3"
msgid "“atthi nu kho, bhante, jātassa aññatra jarāmaraṇā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, for someone who has been reborn, is there anything apart from old age "
"and death?”"

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.4"
msgid "“Natthi kho, mahārāja, jātassa aññatra jarāmaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"“Great king, for someone who has been reborn, there’s nothing apart from old "
"age and death."

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, mahārāja, khattiyamahāsālā aḍḍhā mahaddhanā mahābhogā "
"pahūtajātarūparajatā pahūtavittūpakaraṇā pahūtadhanadhaññā, tesampi jātānaṃ "
"natthi aññatra jarāmaraṇā."
msgstr "Even for well-to-do aristocrats,"

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.6"
msgid "Yepi te, mahārāja, brāhmaṇamahāsālā … pe …"
msgstr "brahmins,"

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.7"
msgid ""
"gahapatimahāsālā aḍḍhā mahaddhanā mahābhogā pahūtajātarūparajatā "
"pahūtavittūpakaraṇā pahūtadhanadhaññā, tesampi jātānaṃ natthi aññatra "
"jarāmaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, "
"lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain—when they’re born, "
"there’s nothing apart from old age and death."

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.8"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, mahārāja, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā "
"ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, "
"tesampāyaṃ kāyo bhedanadhammo nikkhepanadhammo”ti."
msgstr ""
"Even for mendicants who are perfected—who have ended the defilements, "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and "
"are rightly freed through enlightenment—their bodies are liable to break up "
"and be laid to rest."

msgctxt "sn3.3:1.9"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. …"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.3:2.1"
msgid "“Jīranti ve rājarathā sucittā,"
msgstr "“The fancy chariots of kings wear out,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.3:2.2"
msgid "Atho sarīrampi jaraṃ upeti;"
msgstr "and this body too gets old."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.3:2.3"
msgid "Satañca dhammo na jaraṃ upeti,"
msgstr "But goodness never gets old:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.3:2.4"
msgid "Santo have sabbhi pavedayantī”ti."
msgstr "so the true and good proclaim.”"
